## üéÆ How to Use

### First Launch
1. Download `Deadshot Client.exe` from [Releases](https://github.com/Pseki77/Simplicity/releases)
2. Run the executable (Windows may show a SmartScreen warning - click \"More info\" ‚Üí \"Run anyway\")
3. The client will launch in fullscreen and load deadshot.io

### Opening the Settings GUI
- Press the **O key** (or your custom hotkey) to toggle the settings overlay
- The GUI will appear in the center of your screen

### Changing Skins
1. Press **O** to open the GUI
2. Select your desired skin from each weapon's dropdown menu
   - Assault Rifle
   - SMG
   - AWP
   - Shotgun
3. Press **Ctrl+R** to reload the client
4. Your selected skins will now be equipped in-game!

### Uncapping FPS
1. Press **O** to open the GUI
2. Toggle the **\"Uncap FPS\"** switch at the top
3. **Fully restart the client** (close and reopen) for changes to take effect
4. Enjoy smooth, high FPS gameplay!

### Customizing the Toggle Key
1. Press **O** to open the GUI
2. Scroll to the bottom
3. Click the **\"Toggle Key\"** input field
4. Type any single letter key (e.g., P, L, K)
5. Changes apply immediately - close the GUI and test your new key!

